*] Select & Retrieve Roles from external resources like:-

    a] git repositories
    b] ansible galaxy

   and use them in your playbook .

*] You need central managed location to manage and store your roles , so you ensure that your projects use the current version of ansible role
   and you can have the benefits of the updates and bugfixes .

*] Opensource community uses ansible galaxy:- it is public repository that contain ansible content written by ansible administrators and users .

     You can search in :-
        website   :- https://galaxy.ansible.com/
        using CLI :- ansible-galaxy search mysql --platform EL --author xyz --galaxy-tags

*] Use ansible-galaxy CLI to install,list and remove roles from external resources
   ansible-galaxy looked for the installed roles in:-
       1] Same directory of your playbook
       2] Project Roles
       3] In path that specified using roles_path

*] To use external role in your playbook , you need to make requirements.yml file to add any external role in roles directory

    roles/requirements.yml

  - src: https://github.com/geerlingguy/ansible-role-mysql
    scm: git
    version: "1.5.0"

  - src: file:///opt/local/roles/myrole.tar
    name: myrole

  - src: https://www.example.com/role-archive/someauthor.otherrole.tar
    name: someauthor.otherrole

*] Use ansible-galaxy role install -r roles/requirements.yml -p roles

    -p roles to install the roles in this directory
     or you need to update the ansible.cfg file by adding

        [defaults]
        roles_path = roles

    ansible-galaxy role list
    ansible-galaxy role remove




